            "body": "I was curious why this affects OpenBSD specifically and not, say, FreeBSD. The build command for LuaJIT ends up being:\n\n    $(MAKE) -j CFLAGS=-fPIC CFLAGS+=-DLUA_USE_APICHECK CFLAGS+=-funwind-tables \"LDFLAGS=-lpthread -lc++abi\" CCDEBUG+=-g Q= CC=/usr/bin/cc PREFIX=/home/kevin/neovim/.deps/usr install\n\nThe error is:\n\n    make: illegal argument to -j option -- CFLAGS=-fPIC -- invalid\n\nIt looks like OpenBSD make is the only one that *requires* a numeric argument to `-j`. GNU make and FreeBSD make allow it without the argument.",
